title: 14 northeast Indiana students on spring Dean's List
title_page: Southern Indiana: 14 northeast Indiana students on spring Dean's List
maintext:
Fourteen northeast Indiana students have been named to the spring Deanâ€™s List at the University of Southern Indiana, the university has announced.
Undergraduate students must achieve a grade-point average of 3.5 or higher on a 4.0 scale to be named to the list in 12 or more semester hours without incomplete or missing grades, the university in Evansville said in a statement.
Area students on the list are:
Berne: Nathan Bollenbacher; Columbia City: Ashlynd Pleus; Decatur: Emily Smitley; Fort Wayne: Jessica Elward, Kayleen Grashoff, Anna Mullins, Michaela Roberts; Huntington: Josi Barscz; Leo-Cedarville: Malinda Newland; Markle: Austin Steele; Pleasant Lake: Madison Steury; Roann: Paige Holley; Warsaw: Taylor Mills, Aurora Rosas
